{"id":34,"date":"2025-03-27T11:04:22","date_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:04:22","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/?p=34"},"modified":"2025-03-27T11:04:47","modified_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:04:47","slug":"chicken-tikka-masala","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/2025\/03\/27\/chicken-tikka-masala\/","title":{"rendered":"Chicken Tikka Masala"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong>A flavorful Indian-inspired dish with marinated chicken in a creamy tomato-based sauce.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Ingredients:<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For the Chicken Marinade:<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>500g boneless chicken, cubed<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1\/2 cup yogurt<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tbsp lemon juice<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 tsp garam masala<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp cumin<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp paprika<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp turmeric<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp salt<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tbsp ginger-garlic paste<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h5 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>For the Sauce:<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>2 tbsp butter<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 onion, finely chopped<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>3 cloves garlic, minced<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1-inch ginger, grated<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 cups crushed tomatoes<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp cumin<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp coriander powder<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp garam masala<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1\/2 cup heavy cream<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tbsp sugar<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Salt to taste<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fresh cilantro for garnish<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Instructions:<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Marinate the Chicken:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Mix all marinade ingredients in a bowl and coat the chicken.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours (overnight is best).<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Cook the Chicken:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Heat oil in a pan and cook the marinated chicken until browned. Set aside.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Prepare the Sauce:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Melt butter in a pan, saut\u00e9 onions until golden.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Add garlic, ginger, and cook until fragrant.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Pour in crushed tomatoes and spices, simmer for 15 minutes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Finish the Dish:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Add heavy cream and sugar, stirring well.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Return the chicken to the pan and cook for 5 more minutes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Serve:<\/strong>\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Serve hot with basmati rice or naan, garnished with cilantro.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Tips:<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Adjust spice levels to taste.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>For a smoky flavor, grill the marinated chicken before adding it to the sauce.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>A flavorful Indian-inspired dish with marinated chicken in a creamy tomato-based sauce. Ingredients: For the Chicken Marinade: For the Sauce: Instructions: Tips:<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":35,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[3],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-34","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-main-courses"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/34","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"em